text:
Pandoc/Quarto collapses nested HTML (divs inside &lt;a&gt;, spans inside divs) into a single line of escaped text unless wrapped in a raw block. Any HTML with internal structure must use a {=html} block:
```{=html}
&lt;div class="..."&gt;
  &lt;span&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
```
Plain &lt;div&gt; in markdown body → broken output.
Links inside {=html} blocks must use directory paths (timesfm-gasoline/), not .qmd or .html — Quarto does not rewrite hrefs inside raw blocks.

Organized by domain sections (e.g. Time Series, NLP)
Domain label: .domain-label — 1.35rem, weight 600, dark color
Each project: &lt;a class="project-row"&gt; inside .project-list
Project row contains: title, meta (tech tags only), one-line description
No status badge on the index

```{=html}
&lt;div class="domain-section"&gt;
  &lt;div class="domain-label"&gt;Time Series&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="project-list"&gt;

    &lt;a href="timesfm-energy/" class="project-row"&gt;
      &lt;div class="project-row-title"&gt;Project Title&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class="project-row-meta"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Python · TimesFM · SHAP&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class="project-row-desc"&gt;One-paragraph description.&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;

  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

---

## Project detail page (`projects/&lt;name&gt;/index.qmd`)

### Frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: "Full project title"
page-layout: article
toc: true
toc-depth: 2
---


Three fields, each on its own line, wrapped in {=html}:
```{=html}
&lt;div class="project-meta"&gt;
  &lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Domain:&lt;/strong&gt; Time Series&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industry:&lt;/strong&gt; Oil &amp; Gas&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keywords:&lt;/strong&gt; Time Series, TimesFM, Zero-Shot Forecasting, XGBoost&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

Fields: `Domain`, `Industry`, `Keywords`, `Updated` (format: `Mon YYYY`, e.g. `Jun 2026`). No Status, Type, Tech Stack.

### Images

- Stored in `images/` subfolder of the project
- Referenced as `![](images/filename.png)` — plain markdown, no `{=html}` needed
- Source images from Notion: copy to `images/` with a descriptive rename, then delete from `_tmp/`

---

## Home page (`index.qmd`)

Layout: photo + name side by side on top, bio paragraphs below in full width.

```html
```{=html}
&lt;div class="profile-section"&gt;
  &lt;div class="profile-top"&gt;
    &lt;div class="profile-photo"&gt;&lt;img src="profile.png" alt="Marcelo Arita"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="profile-header-text"&gt;
      &lt;p class="profile-name"&gt;Marcelo Arita&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;p class="profile-location"&gt;📍 Japan&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;div class="social-links"&gt;
        &lt;a href="..."&gt;&lt;img src="assets/linkedin.png" class="social-icon" alt="LinkedIn"&gt; LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;a href="..."&gt;&lt;img src="assets/github.png" class="social-icon" alt="GitHub"&gt; GitHub&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="profile-body"&gt;
    &lt;p class="profile-bio"&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
```
No CV link — the site itself is the CV.
